1
00:00:00,060 --> 00:00:05,390
Characters, actions, places, occupations,
and events in this series

2
00:00:05,410 --> 00:00:08,080
are fictional and created
for entertainment purposes only.

3
00:00:08,100 --> 00:00:12,280
They are not intended to urge
or promote any behavior in the series.

4
00:00:12,300 --> 00:00:14,620
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:14,770 --> 00:00:15,500
Aran, say that again.

6
00:00:15,550 --> 00:00:16,590
You want me to help promote a restaurant?

7
00:00:16,610 --> 00:00:18,540
(The Italian restaurant Mr. Thee gave me.)

8
00:00:18,680 --> 00:00:20,270
You want to go back to work,
don’t you, Lookpeach?

9
00:00:20,290 --> 00:00:21,700
I’ve been thinking about it for a while.

10
00:00:21,730 --> 00:00:23,900
I think it’s time I did something.

11
00:00:24,020 --> 00:00:25,010
Thank you.

12
00:00:25,190 --> 00:00:26,270
You really don’t want to get paid?

13
00:00:26,290 --> 00:00:27,010
It’s fine, Aran.

14
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:28,690
I haven’t touched a camera in months.

15
00:00:28,710 --> 00:00:30,780
This is good practice for me.

16
00:00:31,130 --> 00:00:32,700
Let me treat you to dinner.

17
00:00:32,780 --> 00:00:34,400
Call it an after-wedding dinner.

18
00:00:35,060 --> 00:00:37,500
The schedule for the grand meeting
has been announced.

19
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:39,540
What’s going on?

20
00:00:39,560 --> 00:00:43,090
Rome’s going to be ARSENI’s next leader,
taking over from Dad.

21
00:00:45,960 --> 00:00:50,290
SEVEN YEARS AGO

22
00:01:03,340 --> 00:01:05,340
Mr. Krisdanai, you should already
be at the airport by now.

23
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:16,890
Mr. Kris, I’m not getting in there.

24
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:18,160
Why not?

25
00:01:19,310 --> 00:01:20,100
I’m working.

26
00:01:20,310 --> 00:01:21,600
Ever since you got transferred here,

27
00:01:21,870 --> 00:01:25,380
do you realize how many times
you’ve said the word ‘work’?

28
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:26,820
Boss.

29
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:28,600
I don’t like this version of you, Mok.

30
00:01:33,860 --> 00:01:34,600
Mr. Thee!

31
00:01:35,410 --> 00:01:35,960
Mr. Kris.

32
00:01:35,990 --> 00:01:36,610
Throw him.

33
00:01:36,630 --> 00:01:37,900
-One, Two…
-Don’t!

34
00:01:38,050 --> 00:01:38,700
…three!

35
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:49,000
Whoo!

36
00:01:49,590 --> 00:01:50,610
You’re going to miss your flight.

37
00:01:50,630 --> 00:01:51,800
Then catch the next one.

38
00:01:52,100 --> 00:01:53,930
He’s already postponed
his flight back to Hong Kong five times.

39
00:01:54,190 --> 00:01:55,400
If he misses this one,

40
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:57,390
he won’t have enough time
to get ready for school tomorrow.

41
00:01:57,420 --> 00:01:59,100
Then postpone the first day.

42
00:01:59,690 --> 00:02:01,050
We own the school anyway.

43
00:02:01,550 --> 00:02:02,400
Whoo!

44
00:02:09,979 --> 00:02:10,800
Looking for these?

45
00:02:12,390 --> 00:02:13,350
Come and get them.

46
00:02:17,329 --> 00:02:18,100
Rome!

47
00:02:18,220 --> 00:02:18,900
Catch!

48
00:02:26,690 --> 00:02:27,800
Mok, look at me.

49
00:02:28,070 --> 00:02:29,400
I’m way more handsome than you.

50
00:02:29,430 --> 00:02:30,420
“Boss.”

51
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:31,300
Mr. Thee.

52
00:02:32,150 --> 00:02:33,800
(Kian, can you ask Dad for me?)

53
00:02:34,050 --> 00:02:35,800
(I want to stay here with you and Mok.)

54
00:02:36,329 --> 00:02:39,500
(If that were possible,
I would’ve asked him for myself.)

55
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:40,700
(Asked him what?)

56
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:42,800
(Not to leave me here.)

57
00:02:43,430 --> 00:02:47,000
(To let me stay home with you,
Mom, and Dad.)

58
00:02:47,420 --> 00:02:49,300
(Why does ARSENI have to be different?)

59
00:02:49,850 --> 00:02:51,400
(Because it’s ARSENI.)

60
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:53,100
(That’s why.)

61
00:03:48,920 --> 00:03:51,570
PRESENT DAY

62
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:01,400
You’ve been in the water for three hours.

63
00:04:02,330 --> 00:04:03,400
Come up already.

64
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:07,700
Mr. Rome.

65
00:04:12,980 --> 00:04:13,750
Hey!

66
00:04:19,589 --> 00:04:20,800
What the hell are you doing?!

67
00:04:20,860 --> 00:04:22,400
I couldn’t breathe. I could’ve died.

68
00:04:23,610 --> 00:04:24,900
But you didn’t.

69
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:26,730
Kian, you’re an adult.

70
00:04:26,950 --> 00:04:28,000
Stop acting like a child.

71
00:04:28,210 --> 00:04:30,400
Says the guy who’s running away
from his problems like a child.

72
00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:32,310
Don’t tell people to grow up.

73
00:04:32,330 --> 00:04:33,300
I’m not running away.

74
00:04:35,090 --> 00:04:35,659
I’m just…

75
00:04:36,230 --> 00:04:37,000
Just?

76
00:04:38,210 --> 00:04:39,000
Just what?

77
00:04:40,510 --> 00:04:41,700
I needed some time to think.

78
00:04:45,100 --> 00:04:46,500
And why’d you jump in a suit?

79
00:04:52,780 --> 00:04:55,510
You’re making a mountain
out of a molehill.

80
00:04:55,620 --> 00:04:56,640
You’re jumping at your own shadow.

81
00:04:56,710 --> 00:04:57,760
You’re borrowing trouble.

82
00:04:57,780 --> 00:04:58,770
You’re counting your chickens
before they hatch.

83
00:04:58,790 --> 00:04:59,930
You’re worrying over nothing.

84
00:04:59,960 --> 00:05:00,680
You’re sweating the small stuff—

85
00:05:00,710 --> 00:05:01,660
Hey, hey!

86
00:05:02,330 --> 00:05:03,400
Too much Thai, bro.

87
00:05:03,420 --> 00:05:04,460
I’m not keeping up.

88
00:05:18,740 --> 00:05:19,500
-Kian.
-Rome.

89
00:05:23,810 --> 00:05:24,800
You first.

90
00:05:41,370 --> 00:05:42,300
What the heck?

91
00:05:45,370 --> 00:05:46,300
I’m sorry.

92
00:05:48,860 --> 00:05:49,600
Huh?

93
00:05:52,150 --> 00:05:53,100
I’m sorry.

94
00:05:55,770 --> 00:05:56,530
For what?

95
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:59,600
For making everything your burden.

96
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:03,100
ARSENI,

97
00:06:04,430 --> 00:06:05,500
Dad’s work,

98
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:08,400
our family business.

99
00:06:11,140 --> 00:06:12,100
Everything.

100
00:06:14,960 --> 00:06:17,300
Take it easy, bro.

101
00:06:24,690 --> 00:06:26,600
If ARSENI needs a leader,

102
00:06:27,500 --> 00:06:28,850
and you don’t want to be one,

103
00:06:29,790 --> 00:06:32,000
then let things unfold
the way they’re meant to.

104
00:06:34,390 --> 00:06:35,700
I already talked to Peach.

105
00:06:38,010 --> 00:06:39,700
Did you stay up all night?

106
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:52,300
Thinking about Mr. Rome?

107
00:06:53,409 --> 00:06:54,900
What would you say, Lookpeach,

108
00:06:56,350 --> 00:07:01,900
if I were the one who ended up
taking Dad’s place?

109
00:07:12,470 --> 00:07:13,700
I’d just…

110
00:07:15,450 --> 00:07:16,800
keep training in shooting

111
00:07:17,980 --> 00:07:19,260
and martial arts.

112
00:07:20,620 --> 00:07:22,380
And don’t pull your punches—

113
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:29,330
Even though you could just leave me?

114
00:07:34,530 --> 00:07:36,400
That thought has never crossed my mind.

115
00:07:41,490 --> 00:07:42,780
I’m actually happy

116
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:46,970
you chose to sacrifice
for your little brother.

117
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:49,420
Because if I were in your shoes,

118
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:51,820
I’d do the same.

119
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:01,410
Usually,

120
00:08:02,030 --> 00:08:06,300
the second heir can
only inherit the leadership if…

121
00:08:07,140 --> 00:08:08,700
the first heir dies

122
00:08:10,940 --> 00:08:12,000
or…

123
00:08:13,750 --> 00:08:14,740
Or what?

124
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:20,300
Or becomes incapacitated,

125
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:26,860
and the family agrees he’s unfit to lead.

126
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:31,090
If Mr. Rome is announced
as the next leader,

127
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:33,400
people will definitely think less
of Mr. Thee.

128
00:08:36,419 --> 00:08:38,450
That’s the only thing
Mr. Rome is worried about.

129
00:08:45,230 --> 00:08:47,140
So you stormed out of the meeting,

130
00:08:47,790 --> 00:08:49,530
then hid away in the safe house…

131
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:52,650
all because of this first-heir,
second-heir nonsense?

132
00:08:54,290 --> 00:08:55,100
Mhm.

133
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:57,300
Your turn.

134
00:08:57,890 --> 00:08:59,600
You apologized and hugged me.

135
00:09:00,460 --> 00:09:01,600
What was that about?

136
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:02,900
So cringe.

137
00:09:03,970 --> 00:09:04,700
Well…

138
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:07,500
I was afraid you’d be mad at me

139
00:09:09,250 --> 00:09:13,020
for dumping
all the responsibilities on you

140
00:09:14,910 --> 00:09:16,690
while I lived happily ever after
with Lookpeach here.

141
00:09:18,430 --> 00:09:19,500
Don’t be ridiculous.

142
00:09:20,310 --> 00:09:22,000
If you’re happy, I’m happy.

143
00:09:22,580 --> 00:09:23,300
Right?

144
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:24,800
I’m your brother.

145
00:09:26,420 --> 00:09:29,130
At least my reason
makes more sense than yours.

146
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:32,500
You’re worried
people will think badly of me?

147
00:09:33,230 --> 00:09:35,400
Since when have I ever cared
what people think?

148
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:44,240
So what are you going to do
about the leadership?

149
00:09:44,850 --> 00:09:46,500
Are you going to do what Dad wants?

150
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:58,300
Let me ask you an honest question, Kian.

151
00:10:00,610 --> 00:10:02,700
You want nothing to do with Dad’s ARSENI

152
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:07,000
because of Peach, don’t you?

153
00:10:16,620 --> 00:10:18,000
Why would you ask that?

154
00:10:20,590 --> 00:10:21,700
Just answer me.

155
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:34,700
I just want to spend as much time
with Lookpeach as I can.

156
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:40,360
What scares me more than my own death

157
00:10:40,870 --> 00:10:42,300
is him dying

158
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:45,200
because of who we are.

159
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:51,500
Mm.

160
00:10:54,970 --> 00:10:55,900
I get it.

161
00:10:57,040 --> 00:10:59,140
You know how dangerous Dad’s ARSENI is.

162
00:11:00,290 --> 00:11:02,400
That’s why I want Lookpeach
to stay far away from it.

163
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:05,100
And he’s not the only one I care about.

164
00:11:07,070 --> 00:11:08,510
I care about you too, Rome.

165
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,100
No worries.

166
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:15,000
It’s just a slight change of plans.

167
00:11:15,730 --> 00:11:17,200
Instead of being your right-hand man,

168
00:11:18,410 --> 00:11:20,000
I’ll just be the leader.

169
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:24,900
I get you, though.

170
00:11:27,310 --> 00:11:28,210
Love is just—

171
00:11:28,230 --> 00:11:30,600
You don’t want to drag Mok
into this either, do you?

172
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:46,060
If staying here is the safer choice,

173
00:11:50,970 --> 00:11:53,200
then I guess I’ll have to give you
your secretary back.

174
00:12:12,260 --> 00:12:14,100
This is the Lee family’s safe house.

175
00:12:17,210 --> 00:12:20,860
We use it to hide from enemies
when danger comes.

176
00:12:26,940 --> 00:12:29,000
Back in the day,
besides being a safe house,

177
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:31,660
it was a sanctuary for the three of us.

178
00:12:33,980 --> 00:12:35,200
The three of you?

179
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:41,600
You mean, yourself, Mr. Rome, and Mr. Mok?

180
00:12:45,710 --> 00:12:50,120
Dad brought Mok in to be the wingman
of the next leader,

181
00:12:50,140 --> 00:12:51,820
which was still me back then.

182
00:12:54,670 --> 00:12:57,600
Then he became
the first close friend for both of us.

183
00:12:58,190 --> 00:13:00,200
Mok was taught
to sacrifice his life for us.

184
00:13:02,380 --> 00:13:04,200
So Rome and I made a promise

185
00:13:08,710 --> 00:13:10,600
that we’d protect Mok.

186
00:13:12,110 --> 00:13:13,700
So that no one had to die.

187
00:13:28,670 --> 00:13:30,900
Then, Mok and I were sent to Thailand.

188
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:33,900
Rome always left Hong Kong

189
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:36,800
to spend time with us.

190
00:13:49,060 --> 00:13:50,700
When it’s time for him to go back,

191
00:13:53,670 --> 00:13:56,260
we’d hide out here.

192
00:13:57,730 --> 00:14:00,000
Extend our playtime
for two or three hours.

193
00:14:00,270 --> 00:14:02,220
That’s good enough for us.

194
00:14:04,130 --> 00:14:05,400
You were stubborn even as a kid.

195
00:14:07,870 --> 00:14:09,820
Honestly, I was a bit upset

196
00:14:12,380 --> 00:14:15,100
when I learned that Rome thought of Mok
as more than just a friend.

197
00:14:17,100 --> 00:14:18,700
I was afraid I’d be left alone

198
00:14:20,650 --> 00:14:22,400
by the only two friends in my life.

199
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:34,700
But on second thought,

200
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:38,890
if it’s the happiness
of the two people I love,

201
00:14:42,830 --> 00:14:44,600
I should be glad.

202
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:47,810
So that’s the reason.

203
00:14:48,770 --> 00:14:50,220
Because it’s safe here,

204
00:14:51,420 --> 00:14:54,500
you sent Mr. Mok back to your brother
as soon as you could.

205
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:57,600
I guess so.

206
00:15:40,510 --> 00:15:41,300
(Can)

207
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:42,600
(you)

208
00:15:43,330 --> 00:15:44,400
(see me?)

209
00:15:48,550 --> 00:15:49,700
(Smile.)

210
00:15:53,310 --> 00:15:54,100
(You’re)

211
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:55,500
(not)

212
00:15:56,120 --> 00:15:58,600
(alone anymore.)

213
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:19,940
(I…)

214
00:16:21,030 --> 00:16:21,900
(will walk)

215
00:16:23,760 --> 00:16:26,400
(right beside you.)

216
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:06,650
This meeting

217
00:17:08,079 --> 00:17:09,260
isn’t about transferring personnel

218
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:12,099
or expanding our influence
into another continent.

219
00:17:15,369 --> 00:17:23,900
It’s about choosing ARSENI’s next leader

220
00:17:24,630 --> 00:17:26,300
to carry on my work.

221
00:17:36,850 --> 00:17:38,400
You’ve chosen your own path.

222
00:17:39,190 --> 00:17:40,300
I won’t interfere.

223
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:42,000
This is your territory.

224
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:47,100
But ARSENI still has to go on.

225
00:17:51,210 --> 00:17:52,500
Krisdanai Rome Lee,

226
00:17:53,610 --> 00:17:57,460
you must prepare yourself
to become ARSENI’s next leader.

227
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:19,500
Dinner will be ready in ten minutes.

228
00:18:19,930 --> 00:18:21,600
Mr. Thee and Mr. Peach will join you.

229
00:18:24,310 --> 00:18:27,100
Did they say when they’re leaving?

230
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:36,250
Mr. Thee said
he won’t be staying the night.

231
00:18:44,420 --> 00:18:46,420
Then you should leave with them.

232
00:18:48,520 --> 00:18:49,300
Pardon?

233
00:18:52,750 --> 00:18:53,400
Mr. Rome.

234
00:18:55,120 --> 00:18:56,400
What did you just say?

235
00:19:09,860 --> 00:19:11,800
I never thought
I’d become ARSENI’s leader.

236
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:13,900
That’s why I fell in love with you.

237
00:19:14,990 --> 00:19:15,740
Mr. Rome…

238
00:19:16,300 --> 00:19:17,600
If I’d known it’d come to this…

239
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:24,340
I wouldn’t have fallen in love.

240
00:19:29,950 --> 00:19:31,900
Must be nice being an heir
to the Lee family.

241
00:19:34,470 --> 00:19:37,900
Whether to love or not…

242
00:19:40,110 --> 00:19:41,800
you get to decide for yourself.

243
00:19:49,940 --> 00:19:50,800
Fine.

244
00:19:52,460 --> 00:19:55,500
If that’s the Boss’s order,

245
00:19:57,670 --> 00:19:58,820
I’ll obey.

246
00:20:00,830 --> 00:20:02,300
I have no right to question it.

247
00:20:31,540 --> 00:20:37,000
So this is why ARSENI’s bodyguards
have to stay away from love.

248
00:20:38,710 --> 00:20:39,600
What do you know?

249
00:20:41,110 --> 00:20:43,330
I may not know all the details,

250
00:20:43,640 --> 00:20:46,980
but everyone in ARSENI knows about…

251
00:20:47,290 --> 00:20:49,840
the relationship
between you and Mr. Krisdanai.

252
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:58,400
ARSENI bodyguards
are trained to expect death,

253
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:02,450
and they’re not allowed to fall in love.

254
00:21:03,470 --> 00:21:05,900
If you want to stay here,
you’d better remember that.

255
00:21:06,990 --> 00:21:09,300
You made that last part up yourself,
Mr. Mok.

256
00:21:14,560 --> 00:21:16,600
Ms. Mira, don’t listen to him.

257
00:21:17,660 --> 00:21:19,250
ARSENI isn’t that heartless.

258
00:21:19,830 --> 00:21:21,400
Being a bodyguard is just a job.

259
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:24,670
You don’t have to cut your heart out
before you come to work.

260
00:21:25,710 --> 00:21:28,300
Besides, you couldn’t do that yourself,
Mr. Mok.

261
00:21:28,470 --> 00:21:30,060
So don’t expect Ms. Mira to.

262
00:21:31,950 --> 00:21:32,820
Mr. Peach.

263
00:21:33,130 --> 00:21:35,600
You were taught to shoot
with your right hand,

264
00:21:36,620 --> 00:21:37,620
just like P’Kian.

265
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:41,300
But now you shoot with your left,

266
00:21:41,670 --> 00:21:42,900
just like Mr. Rome.

267
00:21:45,740 --> 00:21:47,500
I call that love.

268
00:21:51,340 --> 00:21:53,200
What do you think, Mr. Mok?

269
00:21:58,280 --> 00:21:59,200
I don’t know, sir.

270
00:22:01,220 --> 00:22:02,600
Right now, I don’t know anything.

271
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:05,000
I think…

272
00:22:07,450 --> 00:22:09,000
you should give Mr. Rome some time.

273
00:22:12,450 --> 00:22:13,820
I’m sure he has his reasons.

274
00:22:18,430 --> 00:22:20,700
And not loving you isn’t one of them.

275
00:22:28,940 --> 00:22:30,200
As for you, Ms. Mira,

276
00:22:31,010 --> 00:22:33,000
you’re allowed to love here.

277
00:22:39,740 --> 00:22:41,500
You should’ve dropped me off
at work first.

278
00:22:41,820 --> 00:22:44,600
Now Mr. Mok has to drive me back
to the studio.

279
00:22:46,090 --> 00:22:48,100
We’ve got two hours
before you have to be there.

280
00:22:49,130 --> 00:22:50,770
There’s no way I’m wasting that.

281
00:22:51,440 --> 00:22:52,300
Peach.

282
00:22:54,860 --> 00:22:55,500
Hey.

283
00:22:57,230 --> 00:22:58,020
I missed you.

284
00:22:58,700 --> 00:22:59,700
Ew.

285
00:22:59,890 --> 00:23:01,500
You didn’t wash your hair again, did you?

286
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:02,800
Come on, Peach.

287
00:23:02,860 --> 00:23:04,260
I washed it this morning.

288
00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:07,200
I’m just teasing.

289
00:23:07,470 --> 00:23:08,700
Just in case I was right.

290
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:10,260
You said you missed me, huh?

291
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:13,600
You haven’t come home in days.
You sure you missed me?

292
00:23:14,830 --> 00:23:16,260
Thee’s house is pretty far.

293
00:23:16,370 --> 00:23:17,650
My condo is way closer.

294
00:23:19,370 --> 00:23:21,000
Next time, we can come to work together.

295
00:23:21,540 --> 00:23:23,300
If you’re worried about losing sleep,

296
00:23:24,150 --> 00:23:25,410
how about we buy an RV?

297
00:23:25,430 --> 00:23:27,230
That way you can get a little more rest.

298
00:23:27,250 --> 00:23:29,100
You can even shower here.

299
00:23:31,070 --> 00:23:31,820
That’s true.

300
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:34,200
I’d never be late to clock in
if I came with you.

301
00:23:35,590 --> 00:23:36,250
Oh.

302
00:23:36,930 --> 00:23:37,750
Clock in…

303
00:23:37,960 --> 00:23:38,900
What is it?

304
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:40,600
I was in such a rush to see you,

305
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:42,200
I forgot to clock in.

306
00:23:42,230 --> 00:23:43,200
I’m late.

307
00:23:43,700 --> 00:23:44,430
What?

308
00:23:49,320 --> 00:23:50,100
Let’s do this.

309
00:23:50,420 --> 00:23:52,810
I’ll go left, and you go right.

310
00:23:52,850 --> 00:23:53,600
Okay?

311
00:23:54,510 --> 00:23:55,200
Yes, ma’am.

312
00:24:02,530 --> 00:24:03,820
Is it almost time for work?

313
00:24:06,390 --> 00:24:07,000
Yes.

314
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:10,890
Then let me drive you to work.

315
00:24:11,080 --> 00:24:11,900
No.

316
00:24:13,370 --> 00:24:14,220
Why not?

317
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:17,980
Because we’ve been back and forth between
ARSENI and the studio enough times.

318
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:24,200
See you.

319
00:24:24,870 --> 00:24:25,900
We’ve still got time.

320
00:24:26,070 --> 00:24:27,740
Let’s hang out at ARSENI for a bit first.

321
00:24:27,850 --> 00:24:28,540
Huh?

322
00:24:35,480 --> 00:24:36,700
We’ve still got time.

323
00:24:37,090 --> 00:24:38,780
Let me drive you to work.

324
00:24:39,370 --> 00:24:40,090
Huh?

325
00:24:51,470 --> 00:24:52,600
What should I do now?

326
00:24:54,020 --> 00:24:55,100
I’m all out of excuses.

327
00:24:55,170 --> 00:24:56,600
You should let me go to work.

328
00:24:57,140 --> 00:24:58,600
I’ll see you in the evening.

329
00:24:59,370 --> 00:25:00,660
I need one last refill.

330
00:25:02,130 --> 00:25:02,900
Refill?

331
00:25:03,650 --> 00:25:05,000
A refill of you…

332
00:25:05,160 --> 00:25:06,540
to hold me over until I see you again.

333
00:25:06,560 --> 00:25:07,580
That’s enough.

334
00:25:09,300 --> 00:25:10,380
Let me go to work.

335
00:25:10,410 --> 00:25:11,700
I’ll see you tonight.

336
00:25:12,100 --> 00:25:13,900
We can’t keep doing this every day.

337
00:25:25,940 --> 00:25:26,800
How about this?

338
00:25:27,330 --> 00:25:29,100
I’ll go drink coffee at ARSENI.

339
00:25:29,660 --> 00:25:31,100
Then we can part ways there.

340
00:25:31,890 --> 00:25:32,700
Deal?

341
00:25:38,470 --> 00:25:39,500
You act so nonchalant,

342
00:25:40,460 --> 00:25:42,580
but you don’t want to be apart
from me either.

343
00:25:43,720 --> 00:25:45,600
I’ll have my buddy Mok
prepare you a coffee.

344
00:25:45,660 --> 00:25:46,700
I already have one.

345
00:25:47,060 --> 00:25:47,700
Oh?

346
00:25:51,210 --> 00:25:52,060
Well…

347
00:25:52,960 --> 00:26:00,100
Then I’ll find you a nice, cozy spot
where you can sip it nice and slow.

348
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:17,460
It’s time.

349
00:26:18,130 --> 00:26:19,300
Playtime’s over.

350
00:26:19,610 --> 00:26:20,660
I really have to go now.

351
00:26:23,020 --> 00:26:25,330
After everything I did
to make you all mine,

352
00:26:26,410 --> 00:26:30,100
you still went and got yourself a job
at another company.

353
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:33,980
What more do I have to do?

354
00:26:38,540 --> 00:26:40,400
Give me the car keys.

355
00:26:41,580 --> 00:26:42,800
I’ll pick you up this evening.

356
00:26:57,330 --> 00:26:58,600
Have Mok drive you.

357
00:26:59,490 --> 00:27:00,900
That way, I’ll know you’re safe.

358
00:27:04,470 --> 00:27:05,500
Wait here.

359
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:08,610
As soon as the car’s ready,
I’ll have someone come get you.

360
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:40,780
You miss him, don’t you?

361
00:27:40,810 --> 00:27:42,120
Oops!

362
00:27:54,820 --> 00:27:55,980
Quit fooling around.

363
00:27:56,020 --> 00:27:59,580
You really think glasses and an earpiece
are enough to fool me?

364
00:28:00,900 --> 00:28:03,000
But in that drama, the heroine only
puts on a fake mustache,

365
00:28:03,070 --> 00:28:04,650
and the male lead can’t recognize her.

366
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:06,220
That’s a drama.

367
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:10,650
10 MINUTES EARLIER

368
00:28:10,820 --> 00:28:11,500
Mr. Thee.

369
00:28:12,550 --> 00:28:13,400
My buddy Thee.

370
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:14,900
What is it, sir?

371
00:28:14,980 --> 00:28:16,100
Take your clothes off.

372
00:28:16,230 --> 00:28:16,850
What?

373
00:28:36,030 --> 00:28:38,000
Call Peach the way you always do.

374
00:28:38,710 --> 00:28:39,800
“Mr. Peach.”

375
00:28:40,790 --> 00:28:41,420
Mr. Peach.

376
00:28:41,570 --> 00:28:42,620
No, do it again.

377
00:28:44,110 --> 00:28:45,000
Mr. Peach.

378
00:28:45,460 --> 00:28:46,500
Mr. Peach.

379
00:28:46,760 --> 00:28:48,090
Peach. Peach.

380
00:28:48,120 --> 00:28:48,830
Mr. Peach.

381
00:28:48,860 --> 00:28:50,070
Mr. Peach. Mr. Peach.

382
00:28:50,100 --> 00:28:51,020
Mr. Peach.

383
00:28:56,580 --> 00:28:57,460
Give me those too.

384
00:28:57,720 --> 00:28:58,890
For the perfect disguise.

385
00:29:00,330 --> 00:29:01,640
Mr. Peach. Mr. Peach.

386
00:29:01,670 --> 00:29:02,660
Peach. Peach.

387
00:29:02,840 --> 00:29:03,600
Peach.

388
00:29:09,250 --> 00:29:10,080
That’s perfect?

389
00:29:12,600 --> 00:29:13,700
How do I look?

390
00:29:13,950 --> 00:29:15,140
Do I look cool?

391
00:29:26,190 --> 00:29:26,900
Hello.

392
00:29:27,650 --> 00:29:28,400
Hi.

393
00:29:36,550 --> 00:29:37,700
I’m returning the camera.

394
00:29:40,680 --> 00:29:41,420
You can borrow mine.

395
00:29:41,870 --> 00:29:44,500
If we run into each other
at a studio someday,

396
00:29:45,010 --> 00:29:45,940
just give it back then.

397
00:29:48,220 --> 00:29:50,700
I’m a first-year photography student.

398
00:29:50,990 --> 00:29:51,700
Wait.

399
00:29:52,860 --> 00:29:54,100
First-year?

400
00:29:54,170 --> 00:29:56,940
How did you end up working here?

401
00:29:57,200 --> 00:29:57,900
Oh!

402
00:29:58,030 --> 00:29:59,300
I’m on a scholarship,

403
00:29:59,510 --> 00:30:01,100
so I help out at the university.

404
00:30:01,370 --> 00:30:02,780
I got to know a lot of professors,

405
00:30:03,520 --> 00:30:05,700
so I asked if I could intern
at a production studio.

406
00:30:05,920 --> 00:30:07,300
I do a little bit of everything.

407
00:30:07,420 --> 00:30:09,530
Help out on set and carry equipment.

408
00:30:10,150 --> 00:30:11,400
And…

409
00:30:14,120 --> 00:30:16,250
I wanted to see you,
just like we promised.

410
00:30:21,520 --> 00:30:23,300
I’m really glad we finally met.

411
00:30:25,160 --> 00:30:29,780
And I’m happy
to see you chasing your dream.

412
00:30:30,010 --> 00:30:32,400
It might be a small first step,
but you’ve already taken it.

413
00:30:33,530 --> 00:30:34,300
Thank you.

414
00:30:34,390 --> 00:30:37,300
Hey, how about this?

415
00:30:37,720 --> 00:30:41,100
Since we finally met,
would you like to be my assistant?

416
00:30:41,520 --> 00:30:42,740
I’ll talk to the producer for you.

417
00:30:46,430 --> 00:30:47,300
I’d love to.

418
00:30:57,850 --> 00:30:59,260
Drive faster, M2.

419
00:30:59,670 --> 00:31:01,500
Peach is about to get off work, right, M1?

420
00:31:03,730 --> 00:31:05,770
M? What’s that, sir?

421
00:31:05,940 --> 00:31:06,860
Mok and Mira.

422
00:31:08,650 --> 00:31:09,400
Ah.

423
00:31:09,840 --> 00:31:11,800
According to the breakdown
Mr. Peach sent us,

424
00:31:12,490 --> 00:31:14,600
they haven’t even shot the last setup yet.

425
00:31:17,140 --> 00:31:18,730
I miss him like crazy.

426
00:31:19,370 --> 00:31:20,500
If you miss him,

427
00:31:20,840 --> 00:31:22,370
why not send him a text?

428
00:31:22,400 --> 00:31:23,400
Absolutely not.

429
00:31:23,900 --> 00:31:25,600
I don’t want to interrupt him
while he’s working.

430
00:31:26,300 --> 00:31:27,850
Peach needs to stay focused.

431
00:31:29,620 --> 00:31:30,300
Yes, sir.

432
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:41,620
SOMETHING AMAZING HAPPENED.
I’LL TELL YOU WHEN I GET HOME.

433
00:31:43,430 --> 00:31:44,570
Amazing?

434
00:31:45,650 --> 00:31:47,780
How did Peach call this ‘amazing’?

435
00:31:48,970 --> 00:31:50,700
The company that hired Peach today,

436
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:51,620
buy it!

437
00:31:52,500 --> 00:31:54,500
You just said you didn’t want to
interrupt him at work.

438
00:31:56,070 --> 00:31:57,060
Are they hugging?

439
00:32:02,930 --> 00:32:03,800
It’s fine.

440
00:32:04,540 --> 00:32:06,580
At least they’re keeping a safe distance.

441
00:32:12,210 --> 00:32:14,400
And what’s with that stupid mini heart?

442
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:17,100
Damn it!

443
00:32:20,920 --> 00:32:23,100
About buying that company,

444
00:32:23,470 --> 00:32:25,300
should we treat that as an actual order?

445
00:32:36,940 --> 00:32:38,340
You did a great job today.

446
00:32:38,690 --> 00:32:40,340
See you at the next shoot.

447
00:32:41,130 --> 00:32:42,100
Thank you, Peach.

448
00:32:42,730 --> 00:32:44,100
I’m really glad we met.

449
00:32:44,220 --> 00:32:44,860
See you.

450
00:32:45,100 --> 00:32:46,060
Sure. See you.

451
00:32:56,310 --> 00:32:57,200
The day after tomorrow?

452
00:32:57,600 --> 00:32:59,100
Let me check Mr. Thee’s schedule first.

453
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:01,180
I think we can make it.

454
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:02,130
(Okay.)

455
00:33:02,160 --> 00:33:04,640
(I’ve come up with
a bunch of new dishes with the chef,)

456
00:33:04,670 --> 00:33:06,860
(and you and Mr. Thee
get to try them first.)

457
00:33:06,900 --> 00:33:07,800
Wow, Aran.

458
00:33:08,050 --> 00:33:09,200
That’s very scary.

459
00:33:09,230 --> 00:33:10,330
Are you sure they’re edible?

460
00:33:10,350 --> 00:33:12,200
(Come on, Peach.)

461
00:33:12,940 --> 00:33:14,060
I’m kidding.

462
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:16,300
(Um…)

463
00:33:16,660 --> 00:33:17,650
(What color should the theme be?)

464
00:33:17,780 --> 00:33:20,060
What? Do we really need one?

465
00:33:20,270 --> 00:33:21,160
(Of course.)

466
00:33:21,190 --> 00:33:22,900
(It’s your post-wedding dinner,
after all.)

467
00:33:23,020 --> 00:33:25,100
(Let’s go with a peach theme.)

468
00:33:25,430 --> 00:33:26,780
(Is there anything special you’d like?)

469
00:33:26,810 --> 00:33:28,000
(Just let me know.)

470
00:33:28,270 --> 00:33:29,450
(I’ll make it happen.)

471
00:33:34,190 --> 00:33:35,300
Actually…

472
00:33:35,970 --> 00:33:37,900
There is one little thing I’d like to ask.

473
00:34:02,290 --> 00:34:04,100
I got home too late to tuck them in.

474
00:34:05,600 --> 00:34:09,100
It’s one of the reasons
I don’t want to go back to work.

475
00:34:10,260 --> 00:34:12,900
I’m afraid I won’t be able to fulfill
my duties as a father.

476
00:34:13,840 --> 00:34:16,699
But I know you can handle it all
at the same time, P’Kian.

477
00:34:20,219 --> 00:34:21,300
Even so…

478
00:34:23,790 --> 00:34:25,480
I still can’t help worrying.

479
00:34:28,260 --> 00:34:29,699
Back at Baan Klamai,

480
00:34:30,860 --> 00:34:35,400
Mother kept a little doll
for each of us to represent her,

481
00:34:36,510 --> 00:34:39,699
since she couldn’t tuck everyone
in every night.

482
00:34:44,389 --> 00:34:45,400
A doll?

483
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:47,800
Yeah.

484
00:34:51,120 --> 00:34:52,199
Poor you.

485
00:34:53,699 --> 00:34:55,500
You were raised just like Punch-kun.

486
00:34:59,520 --> 00:35:03,700
Should we get them
a little doll to represent us

487
00:35:04,030 --> 00:35:06,500
on the nights we have to come home late?

488
00:35:08,230 --> 00:35:10,700
We should, Peach-kun.

489
00:35:25,710 --> 00:35:26,700
Are you working?

490
00:35:26,830 --> 00:35:28,570
Are you free the day after tomorrow?

491
00:35:28,950 --> 00:35:31,420
Aran invited us to his restaurant.

492
00:35:31,550 --> 00:35:33,700
He’s treating us to a post-wedding dinner

493
00:35:33,730 --> 00:35:35,500
because he couldn’t make it
to our wedding.

494
00:35:39,890 --> 00:35:43,500
Every second of my time belongs to you.

495
00:35:44,970 --> 00:35:45,900
So…

496
00:35:47,180 --> 00:35:49,180
feel free to schedule it however you want.

497
00:35:55,420 --> 00:35:56,340
This is unacceptable!

498
00:35:59,930 --> 00:36:00,780
What is?

499
00:36:01,090 --> 00:36:06,420
The cast that Director Nuttapong
chose to star in Me and Thee.

500
00:36:06,930 --> 00:36:10,500
One look, and I can already tell
there’s no way this guy can play me.

501
00:36:10,820 --> 00:36:12,780
Na-ra-vit?

502
00:36:14,210 --> 00:36:16,970
For a boy band member,
he’s not even as fit as I am.

503
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:19,700
And look at that innocent face.

504
00:36:20,610 --> 00:36:24,180
Who’s going to believe
he has a wolf tattoo across his chest?

505
00:36:24,890 --> 00:36:26,300
Forget holding a gun.

506
00:36:26,410 --> 00:36:28,300
I couldn’t have been any cooler that day.

507
00:36:28,850 --> 00:36:32,700
This dude’s going to ruin my heroic moment
when I saved you from Wiwid.

508
00:36:37,460 --> 00:36:38,240
Phuwin.

509
00:36:39,290 --> 00:36:40,140
That’s a cool name.

510
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:43,960
Not as cool as Peachayarat.

511
00:36:47,150 --> 00:36:48,700
But he looks…

512
00:36:52,330 --> 00:36:53,300
adorable.

513
00:36:54,490 --> 00:36:55,700
Adorable?

514
00:36:56,700 --> 00:36:57,290
Uh-huh.

515
00:36:58,860 --> 00:37:03,600
Looks like Mr. Phuwin here

516
00:37:04,800 --> 00:37:06,900
is about to become your new lemur.

517
00:37:10,950 --> 00:37:11,540
No.

518
00:37:12,630 --> 00:37:13,600
He’s not.

519
00:37:17,100 --> 00:37:18,100
Is something wrong?

520
00:37:24,170 --> 00:37:26,620
I just don’t like hearing you
talk about other people like that.

521
00:37:28,310 --> 00:37:31,100
On the honor of the Lee family,

522
00:37:31,470 --> 00:37:33,540
I swear I’ll never call anyone else
“adorable.”

523
00:37:33,950 --> 00:37:35,900
That word belongs to my life partner alone.

524
00:37:37,450 --> 00:37:38,110
Okay.

525
00:37:38,990 --> 00:37:40,980
That goes for “so cute,”

526
00:37:41,010 --> 00:37:42,000
“good-looking,”

527
00:37:42,090 --> 00:37:42,900
“gorgeous,”

528
00:37:43,220 --> 00:37:44,000
“pretty,”

529
00:37:44,100 --> 00:37:46,460
and every other word
that could give people the wrong idea.

530
00:37:46,780 --> 00:37:49,380
Those words are reserved
for you and you alone, Lookpeach.

531
00:37:54,460 --> 00:37:55,400
I like it.

532
00:37:56,230 --> 00:37:57,310
Like what?

533
00:38:00,900 --> 00:38:02,500
I like it when you’re jealous.

534
00:38:13,680 --> 00:38:15,000
I’m not the jealous one.

535
00:38:15,410 --> 00:38:16,820
That’s you, P’Kian.

536
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:19,040
Mr. Mok told me—

537
00:38:19,070 --> 00:38:21,400
You got the wrong end of the slick.

538
00:38:22,670 --> 00:38:23,400
‘Stick.’

539
00:38:27,320 --> 00:38:28,200
If I were jealous,

540
00:38:28,490 --> 00:38:30,200
that would mean I don’t trust you.

541
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:32,200
That day will never come.

542
00:38:33,030 --> 00:38:36,700
I know that even if the sky fell
and the earth crumbled,

543
00:38:37,310 --> 00:38:38,900
you’d still love only me.

544
00:38:48,950 --> 00:38:50,800
Did you really think

545
00:38:51,680 --> 00:38:54,900
that ridiculous photo
you sent would make me cry?

546
00:38:56,650 --> 00:38:58,980
I’m not the old Theerakit anymore.

547
00:39:10,040 --> 00:39:13,100
This Theerakit finally got a grip…

548
00:39:13,890 --> 00:39:15,300
and also got lots of money.

549
00:39:16,150 --> 00:39:17,000
So,

550
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:21,420
live the life you want.

551
00:39:24,110 --> 00:39:25,600
Don’t worry about a thing.

552
00:39:29,540 --> 00:39:31,600
I just didn’t like that kid
making a mini heart

553
00:39:32,200 --> 00:39:33,500
and putting his arm around your shoulder.

554
00:39:34,300 --> 00:39:36,000
Lucky for him, I wasn’t there.

555
00:39:36,830 --> 00:39:38,000
Otherwise, I’d…

556
00:39:43,060 --> 00:39:43,660
Well…

557
00:39:47,640 --> 00:39:49,400
Your smile belongs to me.

558
00:39:50,950 --> 00:39:52,000
I can’t help it.

559
00:39:53,640 --> 00:39:56,200
Theerakit Kian Lee is possessive.

560
00:39:57,850 --> 00:40:00,500
That’s why he has a wolf
biting a peach tattooed right here.

561
00:40:02,470 --> 00:40:05,900
Or maybe I should engrave my name on you,

562
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:09,860
so no one else thinks about
laying a finger on you.

563
00:40:09,960 --> 00:40:12,260
You broadcast your proposal
to the whole country.

564
00:40:13,080 --> 00:40:14,450
That’s even bigger than
engraving your name on me.

565
00:40:19,540 --> 00:40:22,500
All of me is already yours.

566
00:40:31,860 --> 00:40:33,700
Your name’s been engraved in here…

567
00:40:34,240 --> 00:40:35,200
for a long time.

568
00:40:42,470 --> 00:40:44,100
What a ridiculous thing to say.

569
00:40:45,210 --> 00:40:47,300
I had no idea
you were this whipped, Lookpeach.

570
00:40:48,050 --> 00:40:49,200
You stole my line.

571
00:40:54,620 --> 00:40:56,000
What are you doing, P’Kian?

572
00:40:58,210 --> 00:40:59,500
Is it a surprise?

573
00:40:59,690 --> 00:41:01,100
I’m so excited.

574
00:41:02,120 --> 00:41:03,700
Ready?

575
00:41:04,390 --> 00:41:06,300
I’m going to uncover your eyes.

576
00:41:08,230 --> 00:41:09,060
Ta-da!

577
00:41:11,890 --> 00:41:12,860
-Whoa!
-Whoa!

578
00:41:18,480 --> 00:41:19,300
What is this?

579
00:41:19,520 --> 00:41:23,600
A small doll to tuck our kids
in whenever we can’t.

580
00:41:23,690 --> 00:41:24,900
Thank you, Dad.

581
00:41:25,400 --> 00:41:26,420
This is cute.

582
00:41:26,990 --> 00:41:27,860
No problem.

583
00:41:28,360 --> 00:41:30,220
It’s literally our size.

584
00:41:43,940 --> 00:41:45,500
I haven’t seen Lookplub in ages.

585
00:41:45,810 --> 00:41:47,770
Back when we were working
on the ARSENI project together,

586
00:41:48,490 --> 00:41:49,700
we saw each other all the time.

587
00:41:51,590 --> 00:41:52,500
I kind of miss those days.

588
00:41:52,950 --> 00:41:55,180
Hey, just a heads-up.

589
00:41:55,640 --> 00:41:58,000
Lookplub’s even feistier than Peach.

590
00:41:58,550 --> 00:42:01,500
So be on your best behavior
when you meet her.

591
00:42:07,430 --> 00:42:08,180
Tawan.

592
00:42:11,080 --> 00:42:11,900
You okay?

593
00:42:19,060 --> 00:42:19,800
Aran.

594
00:42:24,490 --> 00:42:26,700
Don’t you ever miss working in showbiz?

595
00:42:31,070 --> 00:42:32,300
Why do you ask?

596
00:42:39,370 --> 00:42:43,500
Whenever you talk about it,

597
00:42:45,780 --> 00:42:47,500
you seem so happy.

598
00:42:49,330 --> 00:42:52,400
Your eyes light up. You know?

599
00:43:04,010 --> 00:43:04,800
So…

600
00:43:06,780 --> 00:43:10,300
Do I look unhappy when I’m with you?

601
00:43:12,750 --> 00:43:14,100
That’s not what I meant.

602
00:43:16,060 --> 00:43:18,000
You stop taking on projects

603
00:43:19,930 --> 00:43:21,200
because of me, don’t you?

604
00:43:22,500 --> 00:43:24,500
I don’t want to upset you again.

605
00:43:28,450 --> 00:43:30,000
And things are finally going so well.

606
00:43:33,450 --> 00:43:34,700
I’m scared that

607
00:43:37,270 --> 00:43:38,500
one wrong move

608
00:43:41,660 --> 00:43:43,500
will bring us right back to where we were.

609
00:43:48,580 --> 00:43:49,400
Listen to me.

610
00:43:51,190 --> 00:43:52,900
Things aren’t the way they used to be.

611
00:43:55,990 --> 00:43:57,100
I’ll never

612
00:43:58,090 --> 00:44:01,800
throw away the last chance you gave me.

613
00:44:05,020 --> 00:44:06,300
Please trust me, Aran.

614
00:44:26,840 --> 00:44:27,800
Thank you

615
00:44:29,530 --> 00:44:30,900
for changing for me.

616
00:44:31,930 --> 00:44:33,500
I should thank you…

617
00:44:35,030 --> 00:44:37,700
for taking in a lost puppy like me.

618
00:44:41,660 --> 00:44:42,610
A lost puppy?

619
00:44:44,650 --> 00:44:46,220
That’s too cute for you.

620
00:44:46,610 --> 00:44:47,980
You’re not even cute.

621
00:44:48,000 --> 00:44:50,260
And yet you still can’t stop liking me.

622
00:44:51,030 --> 00:44:51,700
Hm?

623
00:44:53,470 --> 00:44:57,540
I never said I liked you, roommate.

624
00:44:57,910 --> 00:44:59,500
Fine. You don’t like me.

625
00:45:00,570 --> 00:45:04,200
But I’ll make you fall
head over heels for me.

626
00:45:06,670 --> 00:45:07,400
Now go.

627
00:45:07,550 --> 00:45:08,700
Check on the food in the kitchen.

628
00:45:08,730 --> 00:45:09,900
Peach will be here soon.

629
00:45:11,290 --> 00:45:12,100
Go on.

630
00:45:15,090 --> 00:45:16,000
Why are you smiling?

631
00:45:17,900 --> 00:45:18,700
I’m not.

632
00:45:36,970 --> 00:45:38,300
This literally is a chef’s table.

633
00:45:38,580 --> 00:45:39,500
Wow, Aran.

634
00:45:40,210 --> 00:45:41,500
You didn’t have to do this much.

635
00:45:41,530 --> 00:45:42,700
If I’m going to do it,

636
00:45:43,410 --> 00:45:44,620
I might as well do it right.

637
00:45:45,370 --> 00:45:46,100
Have a seat.

638
00:45:58,560 --> 00:45:59,300
Looking good.

639
00:46:07,520 --> 00:46:08,500
I…

640
00:46:09,170 --> 00:46:10,900
I did something for Mr. Thee.

641
00:46:11,360 --> 00:46:12,700
I finished it a while ago,

642
00:46:13,250 --> 00:46:16,100
but I don’t know how to give it to him.

643
00:46:16,640 --> 00:46:17,700
What is it?

644
00:46:26,140 --> 00:46:28,700
Excuse me. I need to use the ladies’ room.

645
00:46:51,190 --> 00:46:52,200
Oh, hi.

646
00:46:54,610 --> 00:46:56,500
Why are you standing out here
feeding the mosquitoes?

647
00:46:56,760 --> 00:46:57,900
Aren’t you gonna eat?

648
00:46:58,170 --> 00:46:58,940
It’s okay.

649
00:46:59,010 --> 00:47:00,300
Would you like to come in with me?

650
00:47:00,510 --> 00:47:01,180
It’s okay, ma’am.

651
00:47:01,210 --> 00:47:02,780
It’s going to be a performance.

652
00:47:03,730 --> 00:47:04,120
I’m—

653
00:47:04,140 --> 00:47:06,400
I’m going to sing and play the guitar.

654
00:47:06,900 --> 00:47:07,700
Come on.

655
00:47:07,770 --> 00:47:09,000
They’re not going to yell at you.

656
00:47:10,070 --> 00:47:10,800
Uh…

657
00:47:11,230 --> 00:47:12,300
Please?

658
00:47:12,420 --> 00:47:13,200
Come on.

659
00:47:13,330 --> 00:47:14,500
I’m nervous.

660
00:47:14,660 --> 00:47:16,100
I need someone to cheer me on. Yeah?

661
00:47:19,690 --> 00:47:21,700
I think I’d rather stay out here.

662
00:47:23,540 --> 00:47:24,400
All right, then.

663
00:47:29,450 --> 00:47:30,660
Ms. Panachakorn.

664
00:47:34,350 --> 00:47:35,300
Break a leg.

665
00:47:38,880 --> 00:47:39,780
Thank you.

666
00:48:02,410 --> 00:48:03,100
Ahem.

667
00:48:03,720 --> 00:48:04,600
Good evening.

668
00:48:04,830 --> 00:48:05,550
Whoo!

669
00:48:07,260 --> 00:48:07,800
Whoo!

670
00:48:09,410 --> 00:48:13,060
The song I’m about to sing

671
00:48:13,260 --> 00:48:20,100
was written straight from the heart
of Mr. Peachayarat Jane-kit…

672
00:48:20,620 --> 00:48:21,200
Oops.

673
00:48:21,600 --> 00:48:22,430
I mean, Lee.

674
00:48:23,310 --> 00:48:27,300
It’s how he feels about his life partner.

675
00:48:27,490 --> 00:48:29,390
Aww!

676
00:48:30,340 --> 00:48:31,340
Enough talking.

677
00:48:31,540 --> 00:48:32,350
Just sing already.

678
00:48:37,660 --> 00:48:38,740
You wrote a song, Peach?

679
00:48:42,350 --> 00:48:44,400
There’s just one problem.

680
00:48:45,390 --> 00:48:46,200
What is it?

681
00:48:46,580 --> 00:48:48,100
I did try…

682
00:48:49,220 --> 00:48:50,500
but I really can’t sing.

683
00:48:51,590 --> 00:48:52,600
What’s going on here?

684
00:49:12,280 --> 00:49:16,300
♪ Since the day
I finally found the answer ♪

685
00:49:16,620 --> 00:49:20,600
♪ It’s you who’s worth
more than any treasure ♪

686
00:49:20,900 --> 00:49:24,900
♪ I need nothing more
just you here with me ♪

687
00:49:25,160 --> 00:49:29,180
♪ And you’ll always be
the only one my eyes will see ♪

688
00:49:29,770 --> 00:49:33,890
♪ No matter what we face
no matter how much time goes by ♪

689
00:49:33,930 --> 00:49:37,780
♪ You’re still the only one
who owns this heart of mine ♪

690
00:49:38,250 --> 00:49:43,200
♪ I’ll rest at this place,
right here with you ♪

691
00:49:43,680 --> 00:49:46,220
♪ I fall in love with you ♪

692
00:49:46,360 --> 00:49:49,400
♪ You’re my only focus ♪

693
00:49:49,810 --> 00:49:53,500
♪ You’re the only one I’m searching for ♪

694
00:49:53,590 --> 00:49:55,900
♪ No matter how the world keeps turning ♪

695
00:49:55,920 --> 00:49:58,100
♪ You’re the one I adore ♪

696
00:49:58,610 --> 00:50:02,600
♪ Every second belongs to you ♪

697
00:50:03,490 --> 00:50:06,600
♪ You’re my only focus ♪

698
00:50:06,650 --> 00:50:10,300
May I have this dance, Mr. Theerakit?

699
00:50:10,670 --> 00:50:14,700
♪ Though the days pass by,
you’re all I see ♪

700
00:50:15,000 --> 00:50:17,800
♪ I’ll love, love only you ♪

701
00:50:18,140 --> 00:50:21,650
♪ Forever only choosing you still ♪

702
00:50:29,500 --> 00:50:33,800
♪ No matter what we face
no matter how much time goes by ♪

703
00:50:33,940 --> 00:50:37,780
♪ You’re still the only one
who owns this heart of mine ♪

704
00:50:38,610 --> 00:50:40,940
A surprise for me, baby?

705
00:50:43,370 --> 00:50:44,100
I…

706
00:50:44,680 --> 00:50:46,180
I wrote this song a long time ago.

707
00:50:47,390 --> 00:50:49,000
After you proposed to me.

708
00:50:52,060 --> 00:50:54,540
I wanted to give something back
for all the love you’ve given me.

709
00:50:54,760 --> 00:50:55,900
But what else could I do?

710
00:50:57,310 --> 00:50:58,700
I can’t sing.

711
00:51:01,690 --> 00:51:03,200
Even if you just read the lyrics,

712
00:51:04,580 --> 00:51:06,820
they’ll still sound like music to my ears.

713
00:51:06,880 --> 00:51:10,400
♪ You’re the only one I’m searching for ♪

714
00:51:10,680 --> 00:51:14,780
♪ Though the days pass by,
you’re all I see ♪

715
00:51:14,980 --> 00:51:17,900
♪ I’ll love, love only you ♪

716
00:51:18,200 --> 00:51:21,810
♪ Forever only choosing you still ♪

717
00:51:39,510 --> 00:51:40,200
Mr. Mok.

718
00:51:40,570 --> 00:51:42,170
You couldn’t even pass the first test.

719
00:51:42,710 --> 00:51:45,600
How am I supposed to trust you
with Mr. Theerakit?

720
00:51:48,580 --> 00:51:49,500
I’m sorry.

721
00:51:59,280 --> 00:52:03,220
(There are some moments of yours
that you never get to see.)

722
00:52:03,390 --> 00:52:04,460
(But I do.)

723
00:52:04,760 --> 00:52:05,800
What is this?

724
00:52:07,170 --> 00:52:08,700
It’s our post-wedding dinner.

725
00:52:09,730 --> 00:52:11,130
Of course it can’t be ordinary.

726
00:52:11,980 --> 00:52:13,300
(This is when you’re asleep.)

727
00:52:13,670 --> 00:52:16,240
(You probably don’t know
that you look so cute when you sleep.)

728
00:52:16,800 --> 00:52:20,600
(That’s why I love watching you.)

729
00:52:21,220 --> 00:52:22,900
(Back then, I could only steal glances.)

730
00:52:23,800 --> 00:52:26,700
(Now I’ve been watching you sleep
for over three months. )

731
00:52:47,420 --> 00:52:49,400
(As long as there’s another morning,)

732
00:52:51,440 --> 00:52:54,000
(let me wake up beside you
and watch you sleep, stubborn one.)

733
00:52:57,270 --> 00:52:58,900
I loved you so much before,

734
00:53:01,530 --> 00:53:03,900
but today,
I love you a thousand times more,

735
00:53:05,290 --> 00:53:06,600
and I’ll never stop loving you.

736
00:53:08,620 --> 00:53:11,200
Be my dance partner
for the rest of our lives.

737
00:53:14,300 --> 00:53:15,920
Until my very last breath.

738
00:53:31,330 --> 00:53:33,100
I told you before that

739
00:53:33,820 --> 00:53:36,800
I couldn’t get more tattoos
because it hurt.

740
00:53:39,380 --> 00:53:41,200
So instead, I wrote it down.

741
00:53:46,330 --> 00:53:50,420
Forever Only Choosing You Still.

742
00:54:18,770 --> 00:54:19,650
Let’s go, Mr. Thee.

743
00:54:32,170 --> 00:54:32,900
Whoo!

744
00:54:36,920 --> 00:54:38,000
Over here.

745
00:54:38,120 --> 00:54:40,140
Throw it this way, Peach!

746
00:54:40,780 --> 00:54:41,470
Give me that.

747
00:54:41,490 --> 00:54:42,700
Right here!

748
00:54:42,970 --> 00:54:46,700
One, two, three!

749
00:54:57,930 --> 00:55:00,500
Aran, did you know

750
00:55:00,740 --> 00:55:03,500
the person who catches the flowers
is supposed to get married next?

751
00:55:05,120 --> 00:55:08,100
And this is the part
where they kiss, right?

752
00:55:08,190 --> 00:55:08,890
Kiss!

753
00:55:09,260 --> 00:55:10,040
Kiss!

754
00:55:10,290 --> 00:55:11,050
Kiss!

755
00:55:11,210 --> 00:55:12,010
Kiss!

756
00:55:12,200 --> 00:55:12,940
Kiss!

757
00:55:13,120 --> 00:55:13,870
Kiss!

758
00:55:14,050 --> 00:55:14,630
Kiss!

759
00:55:14,680 --> 00:55:15,660
I know you’re shy.

760
00:55:15,900 --> 00:55:17,240
So, don’t worry.

761
00:55:17,620 --> 00:55:18,840
No one’s going to see you.

762
00:55:29,650 --> 00:55:30,890
Oh, come on.

763
00:55:30,920 --> 00:55:31,840
Don’t block the view.

764
00:55:31,960 --> 00:55:33,620
-They won’t let us see.
-Exactly.

765
00:55:33,880 --> 00:55:35,800
Come on, show us!

766
00:55:37,120 --> 00:55:38,070
Remove your jacket.

767
00:55:38,090 --> 00:55:39,300
Yeah, don’t cover up.

768
00:55:39,980 --> 00:55:40,730
What?

769
00:55:41,680 --> 00:55:43,200
Aw, come on!

770
00:55:44,540 --> 00:55:45,530
We can’t see.

771
00:55:52,820 --> 00:55:53,940
Oh, come on.

772
00:55:53,970 --> 00:55:54,900
Don’t block the view.

773
00:55:54,920 --> 00:55:56,300
They won’t let us see.

774
00:55:58,180 --> 00:55:59,550
I know you’re shy.

775
00:56:00,930 --> 00:56:02,500
No one’s going to see you.

776
00:56:11,210 --> 00:56:14,400
♪ You’re my only focus ♪

777
00:56:14,700 --> 00:56:18,420
♪ I only need you, nothing more ♪

778
00:56:18,490 --> 00:56:22,650
♪ Though the days pass by,
you’re all I see ♪

779
00:56:22,700 --> 00:56:25,620
♪ I’ll love, love only you ♪

780
00:56:25,920 --> 00:56:30,610
♪ Forever only choosing you still ♪

781
00:56:31,400 --> 00:56:34,100
I planned to surprise you,
but ended up being the one surprised.

782
00:56:34,160 --> 00:56:35,950
Keeping the distance
to find out how you really feel.

783
00:56:36,000 --> 00:56:38,660
Keep playing hard to get,
and you’ll be left on the shelf forever.

784
00:56:38,690 --> 00:56:40,300
Like you’re some kind of love expert.

785
00:56:40,350 --> 00:56:41,820
At least I have a marriage certificate.

786
00:56:42,710 --> 00:56:44,490
Don’t ever do this in my territory again.

787
00:56:44,520 --> 00:56:46,100
I can’t bear to see Mok hurt anymore.

788
00:56:46,800 --> 00:56:48,000
What do you want from us?

789
00:56:48,380 --> 00:56:50,270
You feel guilty
for putting everyone at risk.

790
00:56:50,290 --> 00:56:52,150
How could this possibly
be your fault, P’Kian?

791
00:56:52,200 --> 00:56:54,740
Thank you for being strong
on the day I wasn’t.

792
00:56:54,930 --> 00:56:56,300
Because we’re partners for life.

